    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Release the Oil Reserve</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Paul Galant letter on June 23 article urges government to release strategic oil reserves to help stabilize gasoline prices and use proceeds to acquire oil-producing and processing facility to replace reserves from United States sources</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Lawmakers Step Up Scrutiny of Price Increases for Gasoline'' Business Day, June 23):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Lawmakers Step Up Scrutiny of Price Increases for Gasoline'' Business Day, June 23):</p>
        <p>It seems to me that if the government released the Strategic Petroleum Reserve to help stabilize or reduce the price Americans pay at the pump, the proceeds from such sales could then be used by the government to acquire an oil-producing and processing facility. We could then replace our reserves with oil from United States sources. This would be a simple and possibly highly effective use of taxpayer funds.</p>
        <p>PAUL GALANT  Boca Raton, Fla., June 23, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
